whereas.text:
Whereas emigration from the Caribbean region to the
			 American colonies began as early as 1619 with the arrival of indentured workers
			 in Jamestown, Virginia;

Whereas during the 17th, 18th, and 19th centuries, a
			 significant number of slaves from the Caribbean region were brought to the
			 United States;

Whereas like the United States, the countries of the
			 Caribbean faced obstacles of slavery and colonialism and struggled for
			 independence;

Whereas also like the United States, the people of the
			 Caribbean region have diverse racial, ethnic, cultural, and religious
			 backgrounds;

Whereas Alexander Hamilton, a founding father of the
			 United States and the first Secretary of the Treasury, was born in the
			 Caribbean;

Whereas Caribbean Americans have played an active role in
			 the civil rights movement and other social and political movements in the
			 United States;

Whereas Caribbean Americans share their culture through
			 festivals, carnivals, music, dance, film, and literature, which enrich the
			 cultural landscape of the United States;
